responses.text:
Shall I wasting in despair, when spring is budding on the bough?
Though winter’s chill may linger there, the promise of the sun is now.
The river runs, it does not pause, nor questions why it journeys on;
So too, my heart, for all its flaws, must sing until the night is gone.
Despair may knock upon my door, but hope will answer, sure and bright;
For every shadow on the floor, there waits the gentle morning light.
